Personally I use the assertThrows and assign the result to a Throwable so I can check the message. 
The reason for doing this is, for example, when I need to check validations which return IllegalArgument, I can check if the message is the expected one for the field is missing.  

    @Test
    public void testSomething_shouldThrowException() {
    
